-- Greek lenders National, Eurobank hold board meetings: sources
-- 
-- Fri Oct 5, 2012 6:42am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/10/05/us-greece-banks-meetings-idUSBRE8940HL20121005

 

 ATHENS  (Reuters) - The boards of Greek lenders National Bank and Eurobank are holding separate meetings on Friday, banking sources told Reuters. 
 Earlier on Friday, other banking sources close to the discussions said National and Eurobank were in talks on a merger that would create the country's biggest lender. (Reporting by Lefteris Papadimas, writing by Harry Papachristou)